news.title: Gujarat RERA freezes over 1,000 project-linked bank accounts
news.para: The move will impact a number of developers in Ahmedabad, Vadodara, Surat and Rajkot as this action prohibits them from advertising or selling remaining units of the projects. Furthermore, the developers can't even seek credit for these projects.

news.title: Emaar India booked for selling green belt plot to Polestar to build school
news.para: Polestar Private Ltd lodged the complaint against Emaar at Sector 65 police station around a month ago. It was sold a 1.2-acre plot in Heritage One society in Sector 62.

news.title: YEIDA plans departmental inquiry against officials in Supertech & Sunworld case
news.para: The Authority is now planning a departmental inquiry against its legal officer and officials of the group housing department for providing misleading information regarding the high court cases involving Supertech and Sunworld.

news.title: Capgemini to invest Rs 1,000 crore to set up six lakh sq ft space in Chennai
news.para: The campus would integrate advanced energy and water-efficient technologies, utilise recycled materials and implement rainwater harvesting during construction.

news.title: NCLT rejects housing society's plea to exclude land from HDIL's insolvency process
news.para: The ruling assumes significance in the backdrop of ongoing surge in redevelopment projects in Mumbai, highlighting the importance of proper due diligence that needs to be undertaken while selecting the project developer.

news.title: China: Shares of property firms surge as sales decline narrows for big developers
news.para: Private developers Longfor Group, Shimao Group and Agile each surged more than 5%, while state-backed China Resources Land and privately-owned CIFI Holdings gained more than 4%.

news.title: Construction spending falls by 0.1% in USA in May 2024
news.para: The Commerce Department's Census Bureau said on Monday that construction spending dipped 0.1% after an upwardly revised 0.3% increase in April.

news.title: Ganga Realty invests Rs 1,200 crore on residential project in Gurugram
news.para: Ganga Realty plans to fund the project from internal accruals and customer advances. It plans to achieve a sales target of Rs 2,000 crore from this project.

news.title: Small and medium REITs to broaden realty investor base: Crisil
news.para: So far, fractional ownership platforms (FOPs) did not follow uniform guidelines. The SEBI move is intended to address this by bringing existing FOPs under the regulatory ambit.

news.title: Safety steps should be taken in escalators for high-rise buildings
news.para: These mind-boggling numbers attest to escalators being one of the most helpful modes of effortless transportation in public buildings such as shopping malls, metro stations, corporate buildings, transit systems, airports, motels, and many more.

news.title: Thane civic body razes illegal constructions in demolition drive
news.para: The collective area where these illegal extensions including temporary sheds, shamianas built over lawns was collectively around 1.42 lakh sq feet land which is roughly equal to the size of three football fields.

news.title: HC tells Goa government to devise SOP for illegal constructions in two weeks
news.para: The HC observed that various govt authorities and departments were not cooperating with one another, which was proving advantageous to perpetrators.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates recovery may be hard for creditors
news.para: Total guarantees of about Rs 778 crore given by JAL chairman and promoter Manoj Gaur are less than 2% of the ?52,000 crore dues of the group which was admitted to the bankruptcy court early last month, following a petition filed by ICICI Bank in 2018.

news.title: Government increases guideline value by upto 10% in Chennai
news.para: Government's revision of guideline values in various cities like Alandur, Salem, and Trichy has increased property transaction costs significantly. The move was supported by Credai Chennai and faced challenges in registration processes in areas like Pallavaram.

news.title: Kapil Wadhawan moves NCLAT to challenge insolvency proceedings order
news.para: The matter was listed before a two-member bench of the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT), which has been adjourned to July 18 for the hearing.

news.title: West Bengal government withdraws 2% stamp duty & 10% circle rate cut
news.para: Sushil Mohta, President of CREDAI West Bengal and Chairman of Merlin Group, expressed gratitude to the state government for the relief measures but also urged the administration to reconsider the latest decision.
